# API Routes — Conventions

## Standard Route Template

Every API route follows this exact structure:

```ts
// src/app/api/allocations/route.ts
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";
import { z } from "zod";
import { prisma } from "@/lib/prisma";

const createSchema = z.object({
  initiativeId: z.string(),
  resourceId: z.string(),
  quantity: z.number().optional(),
  manDays: z.number().optional(),
});

export async function POST(request: Request): Promise<Response> {
  try {
    const body = await request.json();
    const parsed = createSchema.safeParse(body);

    // Guard clauses first — fail fast
    if (!parsed.success) {
      return NextResponse.json({ error: "Invalid input" }, { status: 400 });
    }

    // Business logic via src/lib/ — never inline here
    const result = await createAllocation(parsed.data);

    return NextResponse.json(result, { status: 201 });
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(err);
    return NextResponse.json({ error: "Internal server error" }, { status: 500 });
  }
}
```

## Rules

- **One named export per HTTP method:** `GET`, `POST`, `PATCH`, `DELETE`.
- **Always validate** request bodies with Zod before touching the database.
- **Always wrap in `try/catch`** — return `{ error: string }` JSON on failure.
- **HTTP status codes:**

| Situation         | Status |
|-------------------|--------|
| Success (read)    | 200    |
| Success (created) | 201    |
| Invalid input     | 400    |
| Not found         | 404    |
| Server error      | 500    |

## Guard Clause Pattern

Place error returns first; the happy path is always last:

```ts
if (!parsed.success) return NextResponse.json({ error: "Invalid input" }, { status: 400 });
if (!entity)         return NextResponse.json({ error: "Not found" }, { status: 404 });

// happy path
return NextResponse.json(entity);
```

## Security

- **Never expose secrets in client-side code** — env vars are server-only.
- **Never commit `.env`** to version control.
- Never concatenate user input into SQL strings — use Prisma or parameterised queries.
- Validate all inputs with Zod on the server — never trust client-side validation alone.
- Use HTTPS for all external calls (Jira API, etc.).

## Jira Sync

- Use `jira.js` (`Version3Client`) — not raw `fetch`.
- Paginate at 100 results per page using `startAt`.
- Match `AllocationEntity` by case-insensitive component name (first match wins).

